# RelayDB v1 JavaScript Reader

This is a native JavaScript reader for the current RelayDB v1 artifact layout.

## Supported v1 format

- 32-byte header
- jump-table pointer stored as `u64 little-endian` at byte offset `16`
- null-terminated UTF-8 JSON node payloads
- text jump table at the end of the file using `anchor_id:byte_offset`

## Browser usage

```js
import RelayDB from "./relaydb-reader-v1.js";

const db = await RelayDB.open("/bacon_standard.relay");
const node = db.get("kevin_bacon");
console.log(node);
```

## Node.js usage

Make sure your package is ESM-compatible, for example by setting:

```json
{
  "type": "module"
}
```

Then:

```js
import RelayDB from "./relaydb-reader-v1.js";

const db = await RelayDB.open("./bacon_standard.relay");
console.log(db.anchors());
console.log(db.get("kevin_bacon"));
```

## Traversal

```js
const result = db.jump("the_terminal", { filter: "Drama" });

console.log(result.visited); // number, not result.visited.size
console.log(result.nodes);
```

## Integrity check

```js
const ok = db.verifyIntegrity();

if (!ok) {
  console.error("Integrity check failed");
}
```

## Notes

This reader is intentionally v1-only. RelayDB v2.1 should get a separate reader because v2.1 introduces a 64-byte header, fixed-width binary index, and key pool identity layer.
